* Because I want to be the best mom that I can be! *
.
That is why I work so hard to TRY and get at least 30 minutes of a workout in.  That is why I TRY to eat clean. 
I will be the first to admit that it is hard. There are definitely other things I would rather do... like sit and watch a show with Carson, because I LOVE to lounge! (It's kind of ridiculous how much I love it!) These boys watch me. They follow what I do. I am their example! If I want them to take care of themselves and love who they are when they grow up I need to be doing that in my life. 
Mentally being a mom can be so rewarding but it can also be so draining! 
I've said it before and I will say it again,  taking care of myself and my body helps me be more patient and kind with these crazy monkeys. 
So yes excuses NOT to do this are always there and there are millions! But my reasons why outweighs my reasons not to SO MUCH MORE 😘

My heart is absolutely full this morning. 
Through every training I've had to leave for over the years since having my kids my beautiful momma has always been there for me through thick and thin. 
As I've had each child, it has gotten harder for her to watch them, especially now with three kiddos and one being under a year. 
Each time I have to leave now, I cringe with anxiety because I know my kiddos aren't easy to watch..but with the utmost humility, pure love, and patience she has been taking care of my kiddos through my training away. 
She has taken the time to bring my daughter to Gymnastics even though it's super hard to bring all three kids to it. 
And she even went to my daughters special day in school and got to play and participate with her during the school day. 
I have been absolutely blessed with such an amazing mom who never ceases to amaze me with her perseverance. 
She is my true hero and example to follow. 
Thank you mami, Evelyn Loaiza, for being so amazing these last 5 years through caring for each of the kiddos through each of my absences. 
I am forever indebted to you ❤️ #momsarethebest #blessings

#transformationtuesday 2011➡2017 😱
I came across the picture on the left and it not only shocked me but inspired me to share a little more about my health and wellness journey 😀👇 .
.
The girl on the left was a mom of 3, 145+lbs and full of excuses! "I'm too busy with the kids"
"Eating healthy is super expensive" "I'm never going to reach my goals" "I'm going to look stupid at the gym" ⬅ my personal fave 😋
.
.
.
Any excuse you can think of, I said to justify not taking care of myself! 
I had moments where I'd start off well but then I'd sink back into that vicious cycle of starting and stopping 😣
.
.
Then one day it just clicked for me!!! I had enough of giving up and giving in to that voice in my head that said I couldn't do it! I also had 3 little babes watching my every move!! .
.
Fast forward to now ⏩⏩still a mom of 3, a student in university, a bikini competitor, starting a new chapter of my life on my own and managing to still MAKE the time to take care of myself! I had more time back then compared to now and I look and feel 1 million times better! I have more energy, my skin is better, I'm happier and I'm showing my kids that being healthy and taking care of yourself is easy with the right mind set! .
.
Excuses are easy...deciding to binge watch on Netflix is easy...CHANGES: they take time, hard work, dedication, sweat, tears and struggle!!! But man, is it ever worth it!! 😆 
NEVER GIVE UP ON YOURSELF!!! You are capable of so much more then you know and sometimes its ok to look back...so you can see how far you have come and to be proud of your journey!!! Keep pushing forward, keep putting in the hard work and you will reap the benefits!!! 😜✌💪 .
.
.
